        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap15.pdf_3_0",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Instead, the consumer protection laws and other laws of her state regulate her business.",
        "bbox": [
          0.13916666666666666,
          0.082,
          0.4975,
          0.11933333333333333
        ],
        "order": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap15.pdf_3_1",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The Federal Trade Commission (FTC) is the agency of the U.S. government that promotes free and fair trade competition. The Bureau of Consumer Protection safeguards consumers against unfair, deceptive, or fraudulent prac- tices. Both organizations investigate violations of federal consumer protection law.",
        "bbox": [
          0.10833333333333334,
          0.13933333333333334,
          0.49833333333333335,
          0.2753333333333333
        ],
        "order": 3
