        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap15.pdf_3_9",
        "observed_type": "title",
        "canon_role": "section_header",
        "text": "Internet Auction Fraud",
        "bbox": [
          0.38,
          0.6486666666666666,
          0.5658333333333333,
          0.6673333333333333
        ],
        "order": 10
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap15.pdf_3_10",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "By far the most reported Internet-related offense is Internet auction fraud. According to the Internet Fraud Complaint Center, Internet auction fraud comprised over 46 percent of referred fraud complaints in 2002, nearly 8 percent more than the previous year. Nondelivery and payment comprised 31 percent of complaints and credit/debit card fraud were nearly 12 percent. (Source: IFCC 2002 Internet Fraud Report) Connect Visit the Web site for the Federal Trade Commission or related government site and find out what is being done to combat Internet auction fraud.",
        "bbox": [
          0.17083333333333334,
          0.67,
          0.7591666666666667,
          0.8446666666666667
        ],
        "order": 11
      }
    ]
  }
